Â· An ideal neighborhood coveted even by locals! A quiet residential area nestled in the heart of Tokyo with quick and easy access to the JR Yamanote Line and major metropolitan centers and attractions. Perfect for travelers who want to immerse themselves in the chaos of the city by day and come home to a quiet home at night for rest.

description: Our latest 1 bedroom with two beds is fully furnished with brand-new furniture, clean and well equipped with modern amenities. This 35-square-meter apartment features a full kitchen and a bathroom with bathtub. (max. accommodation 4 persons)
neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.

name: #1 Discover local life, culture & People/Work desk
description: Hi, this is Toshi, an English speaker. Welcome to this neighborhood and my home. This area, called YaNeSen(Yanaka, Sendagi, Nezu), has preserved the charm as creating a contrast of old and new at the same time. It's because of the tendency to re-purpose older buildings rather than rebuilding. My home is a big house in good condition even located in central Tokyo. I manage this house as enjoying sharing life. In a word, the best place to feel local life in Tokyo.
neighborhood_overview:
Super convenient location to get around Tokyo.
6 min walk from the nearest subway station.
A gate area to central Tokyo from airport.

Here is a remaining authentic downtown in Tokyo. A quiet neighborhood with one of the most vivid local market street in Tokyo, beautiful sakura-lined cemetery, plenty of temples, old and new indie cafes, restaurants, shops and stalls, some of which have passed down through generations, and art galleries, etc. All of them are within 1-15 mins walking distance. So now here attracts both Japanese and foreigner visitors so much. Just lovely area.

- Local shopping street, Yanaka Ginza (10 mins walk)
- Yanaka Cemetery (10 mins walk)
- Ueno Park (15 mins walk)
- University of Tokyo (15 mins walk)
- 24/7 convenience store (5 min walk)
- Supermarket (6 min walk)
- Drugstores (3 min walk)
host_about:
Hi there.
A serial entrepreneur since late twenties. After got tired of my work life, shifted to live my life, not for work.
- Managing a share/guest house
- Business and team building trainer in internship and self-developing program
- Providing communication training and self-awareness session

Now preparing a vacation rental / my second house in a country seaside area.  
Down shifted with less money, less stress, more time, more happiness.

name: 100-year-old wooden house/ 1min to the station
description:
This house was built more than 100 years ago (survived WW2 and some great earthquakes), and was renovated recently.

It is located just 1min away from Hiroo subway station (Hibiya-line).
Hiroo is one of most popular residential neighborhood in Tokyo.
There are many restaurants and shops in Hiroo and it is very easy to access to Ebisu, Roppongi (3min by subway), Shibuya and Omote-sando (within 3km).
neighborhood_overview:
There are many nice restaurants and shops within 5min on foot.
It takes just 1min to the subway station, so it is very easy to access all areas in Tokyo.
host_about: I've been living in Shibuya-ku for over 10 years, so I know the area around Shibuya, Ebisu, Azabu, and Hiroo like the back of my hand. I'm happy to recommend a variety of excellent restaurants - though I must warn you, it's very easy to gain a few extra pounds! During my time as a college student, I traveled solo across Japan from Hokkaido to Yakushima, so I can also suggest some wonderful places to visit. I look forward to hosting you soon!

name: Nishi-Ogikubo 2BR Type-A  2F
description:
This spacious apartment has a floor space of 64 square meters (689 square feet).
As you enter the apartment, you will find a dining table that comfortably seats 5 people at the center of the dining / kitchen space. Across from the dining space, there is a living room with a huge sofa and TV. There is a double bed in the master bedroom, and the second bedroom have two double bed. Wi-Fi is available in this apartment.
neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.

neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.
host_about:

We are really looking forward to seeing you in TOKYO!!

name: SHIBUYA Queen Bed Bright Room
description: Equipped with a very comfortable Simmons queen size bed, TV with Netflix,  and 3 free bicycles, the apartment provides comfort and convenience for your trip. Searching for places to visit is easy with both high speed home Wifi and a convenient portable Wifi. You can relax and have a good night of sleep to rejuvenate yourself after a full day of visiting Tokyo. Clean and bright room, on the top floor with a nice view to Mt. Fuji from the balcony.
neighborhood_overview:
-------------------------
Neighborhood
-------------------------
Welcome to Shibuya!
Shibuya is one of the exciting places in Tokyo - perfect for tourism, shopping, and more. There are also plenty of gourmet restaurants, trendy bars, and hip night clubs nearby.
We love the area, and we will help you to make your stay a special one.

From the apartment, you have a quick access to 2 JR lines, 3 subway lines, and 3 private rail way lines.
You can also walk to fashionable Daikanyama, trendy Nakameguro, and cute neighbourfood Yoyogi Uehara.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Moko._x000D_
_x000D_
I'm a long-term Tokyo resident and love what this city has to offer._x000D_
My husband Rio and I have lived in the Shibuya area for over 12 years and know lots of nice restaurants, shops, and night clubs, so we can give you recommendations suited to your preference when you come to Tokyo._x000D_
_x000D_
I love traveling and have been to many countries. I also go overseas on business trips. Rio has lived in Germany when he was a child and he has also been to many countries. _x000D_
_x000D_
We love meeting new people and we are looking forward to meeting our visitors!

neighborhood_overview:
Since Ogikubo station was established in 1891 it has been popular as a quiet get-way not far from the hustle of the main Tokyo business and shopping areas.
Ogikubo is also the birthplace of Tokyo ramen, and it also famous for the many animation companies nearby, as well as an animation museum, and is not far from the very famous Ghibli museum.

Ogikubo boasts 3 train lines and 1 subway. All of greater Tokyo is easy to get to,as well as Bullet trains to Kyoto,Osaka, Nikko and the rest of Japan.
Limousine busses from Narita and Haneda airports will drop you off close to Ogikubo.
host_about:
I have been involved in the sports industry for a long time and have managed to import and sell goods for skiing, tennis and bicycles._x000D_
_x000D_
I have now retired from These jobs and have decided to join Airbnb._x000D_
I hope to create the same wonderful atmosphere that I enjoyed at BnBs in the USA for you in Tokyo,so you may enjoy your time here._x000D_
_x000D_
And also Japanese Food culture has a deep history, there are many foods that you may not have  tasted before. We would be  honored if we can help you explore Japan._x000D_
_x000D_
Let us help you enjoy Japan ! !

name: Nishi-Ogikubo 2BR TWIN Type-E  4F
description: This is a cozy 2BR apartment decorated with bright white furniture. The master bedroom has a double bed and a wardrobe. The second bedroom is simply organized with a bunk bed, side table, TV and a shelf where you can store your baggage. The dining area has a dining table that seats 4 people and a fully equipped kitchen.
neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.

neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.

We manage studio apartment.
The room is located in the Shin-Okubo area.
That space is a studio apartment,but enough to rest and sleep for 2 people.

One bed in that space is single size.
If you want to stay with two people, we will prepare a Japanese-style futon.

Repeat customers get a 500 yen discount per day!
Please contact us when booking.

We also have one room available for you near Haneda Airport.
That room is convenient for taking planes and bullet trains.
Please feel free to contact us.

I'm a host couple.It's Nakazato.

Okutama is
The forest covering 94% of the area and the river that continues from Lake Okutama are very rich in nature that attracts various expressions.

There are flowers in the spring.
In the summer there is cold river water.
In autumn and winter, there is clear air and stars.
He will heal our hearts.

We got married here and had our first child.

I am really glad that I was able to meet the turning point of pregnancy and marriage and life in Okutama Town and face my loved ones.

Okutama's richness of nature is because I think that it creates a margin in the heart and reminds us of ourselves.â™ª

I want more people to experience the richness of nature and the warmth of themselves and people who touch them.

neighborhood_overview: Nishi-Ogikubo is a quiet, safe, and peaceful neighborhood where you almost forget you are only a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the big city of Tokyo. The town is well-known for its numerous antique shops, unique cafes, and secondhand book stores, providing entertainment for all generations. There are also some parks around the neighborhood such as Zenpukuji Park and Inokashira Park. They are both famous for cherry blossom viewing and their autumn leaves. Also, just a 10-minute walk from the station there is a shrine that is believed to be a spiritual place where you can gain benefits from a mystical force.

name: 5P Family Stay at Center of Tokyo
description: Ryokans in Tokyo are disappearing, with fewer each year. This ryokan is a traditional Japanese inn featuring tatami floors, futons, and a peaceful atmosphere. We believe staying at a ryokan helps foreign visitors understand Japanese lifestyle, culture, and hospitality. Its located 8 minutes from Akihabara Station, 9 minutes from Ueno Station on the JR Yamanote Line, and 4 minutes from Okachimachi and Suiharacho stations. There is lots of different restaurants and shops nearby this this ryokan.
host_about:
Hello, I am Suresh Shrestha from Nepal, living in Japan for 20 years. In Nepal, we believe guests are like gods, and their satisfaction is paramount. Growing up in this environment, I love to meet new people and share feelings.

For 16 years, I have worked at Onlyone Support Co. in Japan, a management company providing high-quality living options since 1994. We manage share houses, hotels, and ryokans, aiming to offer safe, secure living options.

It's located the mid of Akihabara and Ueno Station of Yamanote Line. You can walk to the Akihabara Electric Town, Ameyoko Market, Ueno. You can get Ramen shop, Convenance store, Chianese Restaurants and Halal Foods just in front of the hotel.

If you are more than 4 people, please be free to message to us.
host_about:
Hello, I am Suresh Shrestha from Nepal, living in Japan for 20 years. In Nepal, we believe guests are like gods, and their satisfaction is paramount. Growing up in this environment, I love to meet new people and share feelings.

For 16 years, I have worked at Onlyone Support Co. in Japan, a management company providing high-quality living options since 1994. We manage share houses, hotels, and ryokans, aiming to offer safe, secure living options.

name: 1970's Japanese dorm house
description: Make memories at this unique family-friendly accommodation. It is an old Japanese-style house with Japanese-style rooms. Despite being in a quiet area slightly outside of central Tokyo, it is only about 10 minutes by train from the nearest station to Asakusa, Skytree, and Ueno. You can blend in with Japanese life in a residential area. The nearest stations are Keisei Takasago Station and Aoto Station. It takes about 10 minutes on foot from the nearest station.

description:
Perfect Location!
Early luggage drop-off and post-checkout luggage storage are both okay! Early check-in is fine if the room is ready.

Enjoy your stay just 2 minutes from Higashi Shinjuku Station, within walking distance to Shinjuku, Kabukicho, and Shin-Okubo. Easy access via limousine bus from Kabukicho Tower. The hotel is next to Kabukicho, Japan's largest entertainment district, with Don Quijote, convenience stores, and supermarkets nearby for easy shopping.
neighborhood_overview:
The hotel is conveniently located in Okubo, Shinjuku-ku, Tokyo.
The nearest station is a 2-minute walk from Higashi Shinjuku Station on the Tokyo Metro Fukutoshin Line, an 8-minute walk from Shin-Okubo Station on the JR Yamanote Line, and a 10-minute walk from Seibu Shinjuku Station on the Seibu Shinjuku Line, providing very convenient access to central Tokyo.
The surrounding area offers a wide variety of multinational restaurants, with the Shin-Okubo area in particular offering Korean cuisine, and the close proximity to Shinjuku's downtown area and Kabukicho allows residents to enjoy nighttime entertainment.
Furthermore, the Shinjuku Gyoen Garden and the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building Observation Deck are nearby as tourist attractions, allowing residents to experience the beauty of nature and the charm of the city all at once.
Shopping is also plentiful, with large department stores and specialty stores where you can pick up fashion and souvenirs.
